result.name: Incoming traffic on interface $1
result.description: The number of octets in valid MAC frames received on this interface, including the MAC header and FCS.

result.name: Outgoing traffic on interface $1
result.description: The number of octets transmitted in MAC frames on this interface, including the MAC header and FCS.

result.name: Description of interface $1
result.description: A textual string containing information about the interface.  This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the interface hardware/software.

result.name: Operational status of interface $1
result.description: The current operational state of the interface.

result.name: Admin status of interface $1
result.description: The desired state of the interface.

result.name: Inbound errors on interface $1
result.description: For packet-oriented interfaces, the number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.  For character-oriented or fixed-length interfaces, the number of inbound transmission units that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.

result.name: Outbound errors on interface $1
result.description: For packet-oriented interfaces, the number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors. For character-oriented or fixed-length interfaces, the number of outbound transmission units that could not be transmitted because of errors.

result.name: Number of network interfaces
result.description: The number of network interfaces (regardless of their current state) present on this system.

result.name: Device description
result.description: A textual description of the entity.  This value should include the full name and version identification of the system's hardware type, software operating-system, and networking software.

result.name: Device name
result.description: An administratively-assigned name for this managed node. By convention, this is the node's fully-qualified domain name.  If the name is unknown, the value is the zero-length string.

result.name: Device location
result.description: The physical location of this node (e.g., `telephone closet, 3rd floor').  If the location is unknown, the value is the zero-length string.

result.name: Device contact details
result.description: The textual identification of the contact person for this managed node, together with information on how to contact this person.  If no contact information is known, the value is the zero-length string.

result.name: Device uptime
result.description: The time since the network management portion of the system was last re-initialized.

result.name: Description of storage $1
result.description: A description of the type and instance of the storage described by this entry.

result.name: Allocation units for storage $1
result.description: The size, in bytes, of the data objects allocated from this pool.  If this entry is monitoring sectors, blocks, buffers, or packets, for example, this number will commonly be greater than one.  Otherwise this number will typically be one.

result.name: Total disk space on $1 in units
result.description: The size of the storage represented by this entry, in units of hrStorageAllocationUnits. This object is writable to allow remote configuration of the size of the storage area in those cases where such an operation makes sense and is possible on the underlying system. For example, the amount of main memory allocated to a buffer pool might be modified or the amount of disk space allocated to virtual memory might be modified.

result.name: Used disk space on $1 in units
result.description: The amount of the storage represented by this entry that is allocated, in units of hrStorageAllocationUnits.

result.description: This is a calculated item, we need it to get total disk space in bytes.

result.description: This is a calculated item, we need it to get used disk space in bytes.
